# Code of Conduct

Fostering a respectful, inclusive, and harassment-free environment for all participants, regardless of background.

## Scope

Applies to all project spaces, both online and offline, and to anyone involved in the project.

Applies to code and to communication spaces (e.g. issues, pull requests, discussions, documentation, wiki, etc.).

## Expected Behavior

- Use welcoming and inclusive language
- Respect differing viewpoints and experiences
- Accept constructive criticism gracefully
- Focus on community well-being
- Show empathy and professionalism
- General common sense applied
- Platform rules applied

## Unacceptable Behavior

- Sexualized language or imagery
- Trolling, insulting, or derogatory comments
- Harassment, threats, or intimidation
- Publishing othersâ€™ private information without consent
- Disruptive or discriminatory actions

## Reporting

- Document incidents
- Report to project leadership
- Confidentiality guaranteed
- Prompt investigation and support provided

## Enforcement

- Project maintainers clarify standards and take corrective action
- Possible removal, editing, or banning for violations

## Rule of thumb

Don't be the reason for this ruleset to expand, and regulations to tighten

Thank you!